22:30.521 --> 22:32.219
Last time I
crossed the border?

22:32.220 --> 22:32.852
Yeah?

22:32.853 --> 22:33.852
Yeah.

22:33.853 --> 22:35.788
She might be a bit
older than you.

22:35.789 --> 22:38.353
That a problem?

22:38.354 --> 22:39.394
I told this one about you.

22:40.523 --> 22:41.887
Her eyes went all...

22:41.888 --> 22:43.888
Mmm.

22:43.889 --> 22:44.888
Yeah.

22:46.688 --> 22:48.854
I get hunches
on these things.

22:49.854 --> 22:52.251
I don't think I
have time for women.

22:53.122 --> 22:56.321
You're too busy for women?

22:56.322 --> 22:58.854
You too busy for friends?

22:58.855 --> 23:00.220
I don't see
much of them around.

23:00.221 --> 23:01.721
There's plenty
of kids out here.

23:01.722 --> 23:04.020
What about your friends?

23:04.021 --> 23:05.421
I had 'em.

23:05.422 --> 23:06.621
I had 'em.

23:09.488 --> 23:11.687
Long as I don't get on your
nerves, I prefer to hang out

23:12.990 --> 23:14.055
with you.

23:14.056 --> 23:16.156
Shit!

23:16.890 --> 23:17.889
Trap works.

23:18.823 --> 23:20.022
Little help?

23:20.023 --> 23:21.022
Thanks.

23:21.991 --> 23:23.388
Woah!

23:24.657 --> 23:26.288
Show me!

23:26.289 --> 23:27.121
Keep your hands up.

23:27.122 --> 23:29.121
Ooh!

23:29.122 --> 23:29.723
Good!

23:29.724 --> 23:30.723
Good!

23:31.357 --> 23:32.723
Good, that...

23:32.724 --> 23:34.555
Ragh!

23:37.022 --> 23:37.989
Yeah, that's all I'm saying.

23:37.990 --> 23:40.190
You don't gotta marry her.

23:40.191 --> 23:42.628
You don't want to wait around
thinking something's gonna come.

23:45.224 --> 23:47.189
Waiting's a fucking disese.

23:47.190 --> 23:50.690
Think something,
feel something?

23:50.691 --> 23:52.290
You should do something!

23:52.291 --> 23:53.323
Alright?

24:03.825 --> 24:05.758
What's she like?

24:07.756 --> 24:10.634
Well, she's got ears that
poke through her hair.

24:13.557 --> 24:19.071
♪ If you waste your time talking
to people who don't listen to ♪

24:19.159 --> 24:23.715
♪ the things that
you are saying, who do you
think's gonna hear? ♪

24:24.192 --> 24:29.148
♪ And if you should die
explaining how the things that
they complain about ♪

24:29.193 --> 24:33.868
♪ are things they could
be changing, who do you think's
gonna care? ♪

24:35.293 --> 24:39.929
♪ There were other
lonely singers in a world turned
deaf and blind ♪

24:40.360 --> 24:41.358
♪ who were... ♪

24:53.827 --> 24:55.826
I don't want you seeing that
boy Flemming, and I don't

24:55.827 --> 24:57.427
want any more lies.

24:57.428 --> 24:59.625
I could walk
right out of here.

25:00.393 --> 25:01.659
You can't keep me.

25:01.660 --> 25:03.793
No I can't.

25:03.794 --> 25:07.727
But I don't, 'cause
you're making me a liar!

25:09.626 --> 25:13.192
The lying is up to you.

25:13.228 --> 25:15.126
Maybe I want a secret.

25:15.128 --> 25:17.245
Whatever you're angry about,
you're angry at yourself.

25:18.960 --> 25:20.560
Maybe you're
right about that.

25:20.561 --> 25:21.994
I know I'm right.

25:21.994 --> 25:24.552
Flem says failures
give the most advice.

25:26.128 --> 25:27.527
Is that what you think?

25:28.860 --> 25:30.629
I don't know anymore.

25:30.630 --> 25:32.660
Well even if that's true,
it's not going to change how

25:32.661 --> 25:34.161
things are in this house.

25:34.162 --> 25:36.162
If you're here, you
gotta stay here.

25:36.163 --> 25:37.894
Why punish me
for being happy?

25:37.895 --> 25:40.462
It's not punishment.,
it's protection.

25:40.464 --> 25:42.562
But it makes me hate you!

25:42.563 --> 25:45.028
Do you feel anything
when I say that?

25:45.029 --> 25:46.661
I hate you!

25:46.662 --> 25:48.394
I love him!

26:10.031 --> 26:11.063
What's wrong?

26:11.064 --> 26:12.228
What happened?

26:12.229 --> 26:13.862
What happened?

26:13.863 --> 26:15.429
I need money!

26:16.763 --> 26:18.729
I'm leaving!

26:21.296 --> 26:23.395
Get away from me!

26:25.230 --> 26:26.029
Give it back to him.

26:26.030 --> 26:27.064
She didn't ask for it.

26:27.065 --> 26:28.063
Give it back to him!

26:28.064 --> 26:29.730
She, she didn't...

26:29.731 --> 26:31.164
You're not going anywhere!

26:32.132 --> 26:32.697
Shh.

26:32.698 --> 26:33.962
I hate you!

26:33.963 --> 26:35.731
What am I supposed to do?

26:35.732 --> 26:38.297
I need him!

26:43.731 --> 26:45.397
Look at our lives!

26:45.398 --> 26:47.364
You failed us!

26:47.365 --> 26:50.864
You failed your family!

28:04.135 --> 28:05.866
Oh no.

28:05.867 --> 28:08.501
The machine!

28:08.502 --> 28:10.300
It's gone!

28:32.968 --> 28:34.702
What did my boy do now?

28:34.703 --> 28:35.702
Nothing, Sam.

28:36.869 --> 28:39.735
I just wanted to finish a
conversation he and I had
started.

28:40.903 --> 28:43.535
You have any luck
with that pipeline?

28:45.804 --> 28:47.203
Nah.

28:47.204 --> 28:49.003
Don't have much
to offer him.

28:50.304 --> 28:52.703
I'm trying to
keep my distance.

28:54.837 --> 28:57.170
Well, that's fallow anyway.

28:57.171 --> 28:58.704
Don't know what's
left of it.

28:58.705 --> 29:00.470
All's is.

29:00.471 --> 29:02.569
I guess I mean to
say it's infertile.

29:02.570 --> 29:06.135
Even if the water comes, I'd
still be stuck running these

29:06.136 --> 29:07.775
bird races and auctions
and what have you.

29:10.437 --> 29:11.876
Don't think Flemming
knows it's dead.

29:13.904 --> 29:16.870
You think he'd work it?

29:16.871 --> 29:19.137
Don't know.

29:19.138 --> 29:22.304
He's obsessed with the land
we've lost, not with the

29:22.305 --> 29:25.472
land we have left.

29:25.472 --> 29:28.004
You know how Flemming
spends his days?

29:28.005 --> 29:30.637
He's got his
self work places.

29:30.638 --> 29:32.504
He went up to the
mountain this morning.

29:32.505 --> 29:34.671
Really?

29:34.672 --> 29:37.304
Says he's on a supply
detail for the water works.

29:37.305 --> 29:39.104
I don't know what that pays.

29:40.871 --> 29:42.571
He come back already?

29:44.906 --> 29:46.406
He took my truck.

