31:03.543 --> 31:04.642
And a day's work gone.

31:04.643 --> 31:06.309
Gone, god damn it!

31:06.310 --> 31:07.808
Where are those supplies?

31:07.809 --> 31:09.209
I didn't take anything.

31:09.210 --> 31:10.975
You know it's a federal, a
god damned federal crime!

31:10.976 --> 31:11.875
Fuck you!

31:11.876 --> 31:14.809
Caleb, I never
done you wrong.

31:14.810 --> 31:15.809
Done me wrong?

31:28.544 --> 31:29.576
Argh!

31:29.577 --> 31:30.576
Raagh!

31:32.811 --> 31:33.810
Don't.

31:46.078 --> 31:47.776
You're a dead man, holm!

31:51.343 --> 31:53.209
You won't live out the week!

32:29.679 --> 32:30.912
Up, up.

32:44.979 --> 32:46.478
What...

32:46.479 --> 32:48.813
What happened to your lip?

32:48.814 --> 32:51.246
Don't look like an accident.

32:51.247 --> 32:52.366
You drinking too much again?

32:55.146 --> 32:57.346
You're gonna set
this story straight.

32:57.347 --> 32:59.213
What, with Caleb?

32:59.214 --> 33:01.014
No, those watermen
paid me to take it.

33:01.015 --> 33:02.547
There's insurance
money in it.

33:02.548 --> 33:03.313
I'm promising you.

33:03.314 --> 33:04.313
Look, I...

33:04.314 --> 33:06.214
I know you're mad, but...

33:06.215 --> 33:08.047
You've got this wrong.

33:08.048 --> 33:11.081
You don't want to get your
head mixed up over our...

33:11.082 --> 33:13.146
You know, our other problems.

33:13.147 --> 33:14.913
What?

33:14.914 --> 33:16.513
Conflicted interests, no?

33:16.514 --> 33:18.047
Be quiet!

33:18.048 --> 33:20.481
She's a flower.

33:20.482 --> 33:22.998
Someone needs to
appreciate her for more
than cooking and sewing.

33:23.315 --> 33:24.380
Ugh!

33:40.649 --> 33:43.015
Y-you got any water?

33:43.016 --> 33:46.514
There's no water in
these packs, Flemming.

33:46.515 --> 33:50.214
That's the one thing
these men don't need.

33:50.215 --> 33:52.214
There's bottles and bottles
of that spike in there.

33:54.383 --> 33:55.982
It'll make you sick.

33:55.982 --> 33:57.422
You, you can't drown
a fish in water.

34:00.551 --> 34:02.150
We both could use it.

34:02.151 --> 34:03.016
Just a few drops.

34:03.017 --> 34:04.249
Just a taste.

34:04.250 --> 34:05.248
Anything.

34:06.049 --> 34:08.581
I can't go another step.

34:15.248 --> 34:16.916
Turn around.

34:32.552 --> 34:34.250
Get it.

34:41.485 --> 34:43.184
I know that knife.

34:43.185 --> 34:44.650
He'd never sell it.

34:44.650 --> 34:45.810
Came off Caleb
in the scuffle.

34:49.052 --> 34:52.152
I got my licks in.

34:52.152 --> 34:53.918
No doubt.

35:04.785 --> 35:07.386
I'm sorry I took
your machine, Ernest.

35:11.252 --> 35:14.085
I'm...

35:14.086 --> 35:15.485
I'm sorry what I
said the other day.

35:18.520 --> 35:20.799
You're going to find over
time you can't fix what you got.

35:24.020 --> 35:25.986
It's not my fault.

35:25.987 --> 35:27.985
The state took my father's
land and gave it to, uh,

35:29.720 --> 35:31.553
whatever you are.

35:31.554 --> 35:34.286
No resources, no
skills, no money.

35:37.587 --> 35:41.186
And it died.

35:41.187 --> 35:43.920
Why'd they do
that to my father?

35:43.921 --> 35:45.219
'Cause he's from
another state?

35:45.220 --> 35:47.487
'Cause he's smart?

35:47.488 --> 35:49.554
You blame.

35:49.555 --> 35:51.588
You're god damned
right I blame you!

35:51.589 --> 35:53.754
That land was all we had!

36:08.054 --> 36:09.754
I'm leaving.

36:10.754 --> 36:14.431
Those watermen that
paid me were my ticket.

36:16.355 --> 36:17.887
I don't know what they'll
do to you if you return what

36:17.888 --> 36:19.089
they want gone.

36:19.090 --> 36:21.389
I, I wouldn't' go back
with those supplies.

36:21.390 --> 36:22.388
You know about Caleb.

36:22.389 --> 36:24.421
He'll take it out
of me in flesh.

36:24.422 --> 36:26.388
I'm supposed to be halfway
to the border with that gear.

36:26.389 --> 36:27.854
Fetches triple in
the mountain passes.

36:27.855 --> 36:29.488
Anything does.

36:29.489 --> 36:30.989
I swear.

36:30.990 --> 36:33.589
I swear on my daddy's soul.

36:33.590 --> 36:36.089
Those watermen are the
ones to blame for all this.

36:40.191 --> 36:42.222
No, no!

36:42.223 --> 36:43.589
No, look.

36:43.590 --> 36:44.590
You can have half.

36:47.690 --> 36:49.390
Partners.

36:50.390 --> 36:55.665
If you were anyone else I
would've buried you this
morning.

36:57.391 --> 36:59.948
If I were anyone
else, you'd understand.

37:00.591 --> 37:01.589
No.

37:02.524 --> 37:04.456
Let's go.

37:07.524 --> 37:09.256
Let's get you home.

37:09.257 --> 37:12.825
Forget this mess, cut a path,
right aways.

37:15.125 --> 37:16.124
Come on.

37:17.658 --> 37:20.690
Let's go see Caleb.

37:20.691 --> 37:22.848
When you're done with
that bottle, put it on the
ground.

37:25.058 --> 37:27.256
We're not going to make
it in this condition.

37:27.257 --> 37:28.590
Do it!

37:28.591 --> 37:31.424
Ernest, we're too dehydrated
to make it up there.

37:31.425 --> 37:33.225
Kneel down.

37:33.225 --> 37:34.391
Hands...

37:39.726 --> 37:41.925
Hands behind your back.

37:43.493 --> 37:45.559
Ugh!

