The kid.

40:53.233 --> 40:54.533
Christ on a crutch.

40:54.534 --> 40:55.366
Jerome.

40:55.367 --> 40:56.499
Is my father with you sirs?

40:56.500 --> 40:58.766
Now Jerome, now
hold on there boy.

40:58.767 --> 41:02.723
Ernest, I, I mean my dad
hasn't come back, and our

41:03.234 --> 41:05.865
machine's over there.

41:05.866 --> 41:07.500
If he's having
any troubles...

41:07.501 --> 41:09.540
I know sometimes, it's hard
for men, so if you could

41:12.735 --> 41:13.967
give this to him.

41:20.102 --> 41:23.335
Jerome boy...

41:23.336 --> 41:25.900
There's been a terrible
accident with that machine.

42:49.839 --> 42:51.159
I took the Liberty
with the truck.

42:53.605 --> 42:55.572
Let's get you both fed.

43:41.241 --> 43:45.174
It's natural to grieve a
loss, stud, but you have to

43:45.175 --> 43:48.742
be careful that your grief
doesn't turn into blame.

43:48.743 --> 43:51.706
Blame is the lazy person's
way of making sense of chaos.

43:55.173 --> 43:57.052
You know, I want to talk
to you about something,

43:57.708 --> 44:00.841
now you're the man.

44:00.842 --> 44:02.600
I know how you feel
about that machine, yeah?

44:04.742 --> 44:05.375
But...

44:06.375 --> 44:08.608
We can both see it's, uh...

44:09.608 --> 44:12.725
I guess what I'm trying to
say is I'm thinking I could

44:12.743 --> 44:15.408
stick with that supply work,
try and get some of that

44:15.409 --> 44:16.742
water down here.

44:16.743 --> 44:18.507
That's not going to happen.

44:18.508 --> 44:20.940
My father tried
a hundred times.

44:20.941 --> 44:23.275
I know, I know.

44:23.276 --> 44:24.042
You're probably right.

44:24.043 --> 44:26.843
I just...

44:26.844 --> 44:29.008
I just figured maybe it just
sort of needs a, you know, a

44:29.009 --> 44:31.375
fresh face.

44:31.376 --> 44:33.676
Maybe we can try
just one more time.

44:33.677 --> 44:35.309
I know you would
never give up.

44:36.477 --> 44:39.774
Well, I'd like to help.

44:41.411 --> 44:44.043
Maybe it'll be a gift.

44:44.044 --> 44:47.280
My gift to you,
my gift to Mary.

44:48.075 --> 44:49.076
My gift to your nephew.

44:51.444 --> 44:52.908
What?

44:52.909 --> 44:54.410
It could be a niece.

44:54.411 --> 44:56.043
I think it's too
small yet to know.

44:58.909 --> 45:00.242
Really?

45:00.411 --> 45:02.609
Yeah.

45:02.610 --> 45:06.008
I've been called a lot of
names but "daddy" ain't one of
them.

45:06.811 --> 45:07.849
She wanted me to tell you.

45:13.845 --> 45:15.776
I really love her, stud.

45:15.777 --> 45:17.776
What do you say?

45:18.879 --> 45:23.311
Imagine what that water
could do for this land.

45:26.911 --> 45:30.910
If you go up there,
don't drink with them.

45:46.545 --> 45:48.778
Must be trying work up here.

45:48.779 --> 45:51.346
Easy to think the loneliness
and isolation could make a

45:51.347 --> 45:53.011
man savage.

45:53.012 --> 45:56.046
And without women
to cut the grease...

45:56.047 --> 45:57.678
Must make you mad.

45:57.679 --> 46:00.846
What would you know
about it, home grown?

46:00.847 --> 46:02.005
Look what you've
accomplished.

46:03.581 --> 46:06.679
It's amazing what men can
do when they put their heads
together.

46:06.680 --> 46:10.716
I can't rub out a flame
with two sticks, but this...

46:10.847 --> 46:11.946
You've come a long way.

46:15.613 --> 46:17.091
Not without its costs
though, I guess.

46:19.679 --> 46:20.446
Ernest holm...

46:22.946 --> 46:25.411
I guess they call
it a tragedy.

46:26.215 --> 46:29.048
Mm.

46:29.049 --> 46:31.547
I don't like those
kinds of machines.

46:31.548 --> 46:34.448
Drag a man to his death.

46:34.449 --> 46:37.079
It don't make sense.

46:37.080 --> 46:38.279
How do you think
his kids feel?

46:41.581 --> 46:45.498
Look, I know Ernest wronged
something by you all.

46:45.515 --> 46:48.348
You know it seems like these
challenges at the times make

46:48.349 --> 46:51.047
honest people confused
in their choosing.

46:51.048 --> 46:53.681
You know, I like to see
to myself sometimes.

46:53.682 --> 46:56.948
Like we agreed, it can make
you savage, put your hands

46:56.949 --> 47:00.348
on a man, just bloody
someone for an idea.

47:00.350 --> 47:02.015
Not saying it's not without
cause, you know, a man

47:02.016 --> 47:05.452
steals from me,
steals pure survival?

47:06.050 --> 47:08.781
You know, a beating
seems in the lines.

47:08.783 --> 47:09.782
Sound like rhymes.

47:11.383 --> 47:12.449
Just saying the
way I hear it.

47:12.450 --> 47:13.682
Talk talk.

47:13.683 --> 47:16.782
About what?

47:16.783 --> 47:18.849
About...

47:18.850 --> 47:23.015
What you did to Ernest
that night before he died.

47:26.350 --> 47:29.283
If you want, I can tell
those kids exactly what

47:29.284 --> 47:30.282
happened that night.

47:32.016 --> 47:33.016
What's that?

47:41.217 --> 47:43.250
Turned up in his effects.

47:43.251 --> 47:44.689
Family's thinking
"what in the hell?"

47:47.051 --> 47:49.283
And your boys talking up here
keep lathering the tale.

47:49.284 --> 47:51.563
You know, sounds like one
hell of a fight between you two.

47:52.951 --> 47:55.917
Who knows what to believe?

47:55.918 --> 47:58.183
If I'd set to do something
to Ernest holm, it wouldn't

47:58.184 --> 48:00.550
amount to concussion, and
that's the god damned "talk

48:00.551 --> 48:03.784
talk" as you put it.

48:03.785 --> 48:05.150
Now what do you want?

48:07.150 --> 48:09.016
Water.

48:11.285 --> 48:13.585
And what in the hell are
you going to do with that?

48:13.586 --> 48:15.384
The land is sick.

48:15.385 --> 48:16.552
